Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[HEARTBEAT]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.86,0:00:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: {\i1}Abstract image of an eye.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.77,0:00:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ PERCUSSION AND SYNTH STARTS ♪ ]\NAm I crazy? Am I blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.24,0:00:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I be hard or should I be kind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.16,0:00:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as I stand and shake my head?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For no one knows what I see,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.59,0:00:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,yet I am always there to please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.55,0:00:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colours wash over the screen.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ MUSIC RISES ♪ ]\NMILES: They're not real,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.31,0:00:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or they're more real,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,should I say than,\Nmaybe a sighted person can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.32,0:00:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably do without realising,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can feel when things are there,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.63,0:00:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you're not touching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn,\Nas someone who can't see at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to rely on that feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.28,0:00:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It, you know, it saves you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.70,0:00:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And these hallucinations are so,\Nso real,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.58,0:00:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ MUSIC CLIMAXES ♪ ]\Nyes, you can see them,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but you also... feel them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.00,0:00:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ MUSIC STOPS SUDDENLY AND FADES ♪ ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,NARRATOR: Aspectum
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: {\i1}I'm Miles.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.56,0:01:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,\N{\i1}I'm at the empty cricket stadium.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.86,0:01:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DISTANT SHOUTING ]\NStarted playing County
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.74,0:01:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then started playing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,International England cricket\Nfrom '98 through 2008.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BALL THUDDING ]\NIt's a lot of really good fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.08,0:01:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was...\NGot to see places around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.03,0:01:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wouldn't have been able to see\Nhad I been able to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.26,0:01:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Through just playing cricket,\Nthe sport that I've loved since I was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.17,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ LAWN MOVER ]\Nas far back as I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.12,0:01:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad, when I was five years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.37,0:01:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,sat on the sofa with him\Nexplaining fielding positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.80,0:01:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 18 months old,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.98,0:01:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my mom noticed that the pupil in my right eye
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.69,0:01:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't working properly\Nwhen she turned the lights on and off,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.40,0:01:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and took me off down to the doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.98,0:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[ CRACKLING NOISE ]\NThen...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,went straight down there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.28,0:01:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and was diagnosed with Retina Blastoma,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.24,0:01:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a cancer of the retina.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.49,0:02:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ NOISE BUILDING ]\NIt was in both eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.03,0:02:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was much further progressed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.65,0:02:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in my right eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.30,0:02:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So far so\Nthey had to remove that eye instantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.22,0:02:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They reckoned that five weeks later,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.13,0:02:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the cancer would have been into the optic nerve
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.97,0:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brain\Nand that would have been {\i1}it{\i}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would be the end of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.30,0:02:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[ STADIUM AMBIENCE AND SINE WAVE ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I did radiotherapy on my left eye\Nfor the next three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.12,0:02:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cobalt plaques on the back of the eyeball\Nand all that sort of stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and fry the cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.24,0:02:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end, it didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was too resilient.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So they took my left eye\Nwhen I was four and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.04,0:02:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ CRACKLING NOISE STARTS ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.98,0:02:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: {\i1}I'm Nina.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I developed a sight condition\Nwhen I was two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.37,0:02:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught the flu virus\Nand it attacked my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It left me with different problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:03:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost my right eye 13 years ago\Nin an accident at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ CLINKING ]\NAnd then I lost the retina out of the left eye
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.45,0:03:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up to four years ago now
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.78,0:03:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in an accident at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DEEP DRONE ]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That morning I was taking too much on,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[ KETTLE WHISTLING ]\Ndoing the payroll for the staff at the cafe,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.10,0:03:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to get my son ready for school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.83,0:03:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I bent over,\Nbasically caught the corner of the TV
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it burst a hole in the top of my eyeball.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I knew straight away\Nthe site just, it went just black.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just like lines of lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DRONE SWELLING ]\NAnd I just knew. I knew that the site had gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.58,0:03:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was quite frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.98,0:03:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I came around from surgery\Nand I just saw waves of blue and red
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.10,0:03:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.11,0:03:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"They've saved something that I can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can see something\Nthey've saved some of my sight."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.10,0:03:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor came back\Nand I remember these words,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.70,0:04:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,he said: "I can reassure you\Nwe haven't saved your sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"it's just your mind playing tricks on you."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So those words kind of haunted me\Nbecause I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, I can see something,\Nthere's something there for sure."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ SINE WAVES FADE IN ]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he said that to me\NI was really scared to tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ FLOWING WATER ]\N{\i1}Waves of blue, yellow, and green wash over the screen.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.02,0:04:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The images started to develop from that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started seeing patterns\Nand shapes and the colours,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the blue and red turned into\Ngreen and yellow and pink and purple,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they started forming shapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they became faces\Nand the faces were
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.64,0:04:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of turned into like a skull,\Na zombie skull
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.70,0:04:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had no eyes in the sockets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.56,0:04:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had blood dripping down the cheeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DISSONANT SOUNDS ]\NIt just become too scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just sat there crying,\Nkind of huddled on the sofa in the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.54,0:04:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just scared of these zombies that were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here's some artwork I made of the skulls.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.74,0:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: {\i1}We enter a doll's house recreation\Nof my childhood home.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ EERIE PIANO\NAND REVERSED SOUNDS STARTS ♪ ]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I first started getting hallucinations\Nwhen I was probably about four.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was just before\NI totally lost my sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine have always been\Nwhat I've always called "monsters".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.66,0:05:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ones that were good,\Nones that were friendly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[ STAIRS CREAK ]\Nones that weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.44,0:05:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess the friendly ones,\Nthey just sort of sat back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They were never a threat.\N[ WHOOSHES ]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.10,0:05:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There were two in particular I remember\Nwhen I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were sort of snakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.66,0:05:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[ HISSES ]\Nand they were not friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.78,0:05:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They... were as thick as your arm,\Nand they had kind of thick, wormy hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.82,0:05:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're a child,\Nand your parents have gone out,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and your grandparents\Nare sitting for the evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.76,0:06:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've gone to bed,\Nsometimes, you know, as a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.00,0:06:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd wake up and go:\N"Oh, I want me mum, I want me dad!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.27,0:06:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.37,0:06:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't go to the door to call downstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to my gran or my granddad or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.61,0:06:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because as soon as I opened the door a crack...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.20,0:06:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[ STEPS CREAK ]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.78,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DRUMS START ]\None or both of these snakes would be outside
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.76,0:06:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'd try and come through the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you might whip it open, shout, slam it,\Nand dive back into bed again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but you probably wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.44,0:06:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you either just shouted a lot from there\Nor you bottled everything up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and got under the duvet\Nwhere you couldn't see,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,metaphorically speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that works for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.03,0:06:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm seeing a monster,\Nif I cover my eyes, I can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Work that one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.00,0:06:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: {\i1}I walk through a mirror maze with my cane,\Nreflections of myself appearing and disappearing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It does have an impact\Nand I know some days I feel like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ PERCUSSIONS ]\N"God, I just can't carry on. I'm just this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.02,0:06:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't cope with this anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.38,0:06:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to shut, I need to close,\NI need to go away,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.76,0:07:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get away, I need to escape it\Nand I can't escape it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.38,0:07:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's there and I have\Nthem bad days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So for me,\NI experience them all day, every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the moment I waked,\Nto the moment I get to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.60,0:07:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or when I get to sleep\Nbecause that is one thing that I struggle with,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.87,0:07:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,getting to sleep\Nbecause when the hallucinations are there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they're there when I close my eyes,\Nthey don't go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It drives me insane sometimes. \N[LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I just, like... I know it sounds,\Nand I probably shouldn't say this in front of everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but it sounds like some days,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.40,0:07:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially it's more at nighttime
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.64,0:07:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when I'm trying to get to sleep, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I smack myself on the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.29,0:07:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I shake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.16,0:07:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I lie there in bed crying,\Nbegging for it to go away
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.11,0:07:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because I just want to go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.98,0:07:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is really difficult to live with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you can't make it go away,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.91,0:08:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you know, and then you feel,\Nthen you get guilt and shame
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for whacking yourself on the head\Nto try and make it go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it can be so lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.52,0:08:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nnobody knows what I'm going through,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no one can see what I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to explain it to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know if they're going to think\Nyou're crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.47,0:08:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or they're gonna empathise,\Nor they're gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.16,0:08:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't know how they're going to react.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.88,0:08:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: {\i1}I'm sitting in the garden with NUSHKA,{\i}\N{\i1}my German Shepherd guide dog.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.08,0:08:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING; DOG WHINING ]\NHow do you tell someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I really don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just something that I lived with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told a friend of mine  
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about them probably when I was about\Nseven, six, seven, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not “Oh, I see these monsters”,\Nit was just: “There are these monsters”.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.04,0:08:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I suspect at that age he probably
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:08:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]\Ntook it as a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.24,0:09:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But also I think he probably\Nknew to a point there was something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.96,0:09:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he would ask, he'd say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"What monsters are there today?\NWhich ones are they? Let's get them!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING; DOG WHINING ]\NAnd we'd charge down the corridor,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.38,0:09:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d attack these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and it actually felt quite good,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.41,0:09:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,just to actually be on the front foot,\Nfelt…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.15,0:09:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[ EXHALES ]\Nfelt good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.39,0:09:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ DOG WHINING ]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ WATER FLOWING ]\NNINA: {\i1}Reflections of images through water.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.72,0:09:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ MELANCHOLIC SYNTHS ♪ ]\NFrom the moment I was told
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was just my mind,\Nand I saw those wavy colours,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it was probably about five or six weeks that I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,kept it to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.56,0:09:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is... doesn't seem \Nthat long but for me, it felt like...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.03,0:09:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,months.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.72,0:09:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it got to the point where I just,\Nlike, I can't do this alone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.64,0:09:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to speak to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was really scared of telling anyone,\Nbecause I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:09:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“They're going to think I'm going mad."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.96,0:10:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"What you mean you can see someone\Nin the corner of the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.40,0:10:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"What do you mean you can see a crocodile\Ncrawling across the living room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.27,0:10:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are you going crazy? You're mental?”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gonna think\Nthat I'm having a nervous breakdown,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've lost my sight,\Nand I've lost my business
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've lost, you know…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,stick me on a load of tablets,\Nand I'm just going to become a vegetable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.76,0:10:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in the corner of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I was really scared\Nto tell anyone. So I told my mom and husband
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.00,0:10:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and they didn't have a clue, but they were\Nreally understanding and patient and  
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.60,0:10:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"Right let's try\Nand find out what's going on."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.30,0:10:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when I came across\NJudith Potts and Esme's Umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.92,0:10:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]\NSo, I emailed her
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.95,0:10:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and explained what I was going through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.19,0:10:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and she replied and said
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.00,0:10:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, you've got Charles Bonnet syndrome."\NAnd I was like "Wooh, what's that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It just felt amazing that\Nshe's told me that I have this condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got a name. Wow!\NEven though I had no idea what it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.02,0:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I had something that had a name,\Nand a partial explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ ORCHESTRAL MUSIC ♪ ]\NMILES: {\i1}Back in the doll's house,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a documentary is playing on TV.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.00,0:11:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We hear from Judith Potts, Prof{\i}\N{\i1}Mariya Moosajee, and Prof Dominic Ffytche.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,JUDITH ON TV: {\i1}When you full sight, there\Nare messages which run all the time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.33,0:11:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from the retina in the eye\Nto the visual cortex in the brain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.48,0:11:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The eye acting like a camera and the brain\Ninterpreting what it is you're seeing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.44,0:11:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When sight diminishes,\Nthose messages slow down{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.08,0:11:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or stop entirely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.61,0:11:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the brain doesn't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.34,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The brain doesn't kind of retire at that\Npoint, the brain, with nothing to interpret {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}fires up, and creates its own images,\Nwhich are the visual hallucinations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.00,0:11:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,MARIYA ON TV: {\i1}These are\Npurely visual hallucinations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.57,0:11:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and they're not linked\Nto any kind of mental illness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.83,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Charles Bonnet syndrome is a side effect{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.81,0:12:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of losing one's vision, and\Nit manifests as visual hallucinations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.52,0:12:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you could imagine,\Nif you're looking at your surroundings{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.84,0:12:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and part of your eye isn't working\Nproperly, and it can't see very well,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.02,0:12:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it could be like a jigsaw.\NThere are parts of the jigsaw with the pieces there{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.56,0:12:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then there are dark bits,\Nwhere the pieces aren't present.  {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.56,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your brain realises\Nthat there are gaps in  {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}your vision, and it tries to fill\Nthose gaps with an image.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,DOMINIC ON TV:\N{\i1}So Charles Bonnet syndrome ranges from{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.44,0:12:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}very simple types of hallucination.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.57,0:12:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It could be just a colour blob\Nor a line, to about 60% of people{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.37,0:12:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who will describe a disembodied face,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.30,0:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's often distorted in some way{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and so, people will describe it like a monster or\Na gargoyle or grotesque in some way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then we get into sort of the rarer types.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.35,0:12:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}About a third of people will see\Nactual text or a sentence written there{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.56,0:12:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but when you try to read it,\Nit doesn't make sense,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.11,0:12:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and there's a variant\Nto that with musical notation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We don't know what's special\Nabout that type of object{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but that seems to be a typical\NCharles Bonnet syndrome hallucination.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA :{\i1} Waves of yellow.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.17,0:13:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A white bird moving in the corner.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.72,0:13:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ SOFT SYNTH ♪ ]\NSo, they're here right now with me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[ WATER FLOWING ]\NI've got kind of yellow clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a kind of like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.80,0:13:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[ SEAGULLS SQUAWKING ]\Nwhite little bird floating here at the side,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.07,0:13:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and clouds are moving just gracefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.64,0:13:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can't shift them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, I had\Na bit of a meltdown with my technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.87,0:13:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wasn't doing what I needed it to do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.32,0:13:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was getting really\Nstressed out with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.52,0:13:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when the zombie faces\Nstarted appearing as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they've made me fall down\Nthe stairs or walk into doors  
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.96,0:13:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of a sudden\Na tiger might just pop up in front of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.06,0:13:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it kind of takes me off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.42,0:13:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING; DOG WHINING ]\NMILES: You just don't know it’s a…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.65,0:13:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think about\Nit being a… being a "thing”.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.08,0:14:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a recognised syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.25,0:14:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which, which I think\Nhas made things a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's my experience that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.98,0:14:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the eight months\Nsince I’ve actually started talking about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think they’re as intrusive,\Nnot as aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.98,0:14:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re still always there\Nand they still do have their times,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]\Nbut the times are currently less frequent,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so maybe,\NI won't say talking about them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has cured them at all,\Nbecause like I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they're still there every time,\Njust all the time, they are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.98,0:14:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe it has, in some way,\Nenabled me not to be so worried about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.56,0:14:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: {\i1}Shimmering animations of hallucinations{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.91,0:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}play behind silhouettes of Miles and myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.14,0:14:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ PERCUSSIONS AND SYNTHS ♪ ]\NTo my Charles Bonnet syndrome,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.02,0:15:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just like to say “Welcome”.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our journey has been a turbulent one\Nand I was unsure of which way it would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.40,0:15:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can now safely say you're a part of me,\Nand I welcome
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.10,0:15:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: Dear monsters of Charles Bonnet syndrome.\NSince I was five, you have intruded into my life 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.84,0:15:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,without so much as a by-your-leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was four and a half\Nand lost my sight
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you lost not a second\Nstepping into the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.96,0:15:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In those days,\Nyou terrorised me with many forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.72,0:15:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: When you first came into my life,\Nyou were a stranger, unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You appeared in a flourish \Nof colour and a subtle wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.80,0:15:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You were barely even there,\Nbut as you grew,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so did my fear and loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.84,0:15:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: The number of your forms\Ndecreased over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But none of you lost a moment or an\Nopportunity to try and intimidate me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and insinuate yourselves into my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally found out what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.60,0:16:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the eight months since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've begun to be able to\Ndo the hardest thing  
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell people about you.\N[ ♪ SNARE DRUMMING STOPS ♪ ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: Then, that moment came in a second,\Nwhen, sat there alone, that I am in control.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ SOFT SYNTHS ADDED ♪ ]\NI began to share and tell people more of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I did,\Nyou became a part of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.04,0:16:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned about you. I found out\Nwho you were and why you existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how hard it is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell those that you love, that you\Nhave been terrified out of your wits
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.60,0:16:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all your life \Nand haven't been able to tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.00,0:16:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You bully and intimidate,\Nand like bullies the world over,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.76,0:17:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,once you are exposed yourselves,\Nyou weaken, you diminish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: A breath, a moment, a thought,\Nand I am in control again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.28,0:17:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There are the times we get along,\Nand this is where you show your fun side
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with bubbles, stars,\Nand plenty of colour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I own you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.39,0:17:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to tell as many\Npeople about you as I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.08,0:17:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,, in the hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.36,0:17:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that less people have to spend their lives\Ntrapped inside their own heads with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.24,0:17:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take\Nwhat I've learnt from my life with you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hope\Nthat it will teach others and help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,MILES: In short,\Nyour days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.52,0:17:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.28,0:17:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And with understanding  
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.08,0:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,comes acceptance and ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And with acceptance\Nand ownership comes freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ MUSIC STOPS ♪ ]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.57,0:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,NINA: On that note, Charles Bonnet\Nsyndrome, I thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not so scared anymore. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.24,0:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}NARRATOR: One in five people with sight loss{\i}\N{\i1}experience some degree of Charles Bonnet syndrome.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With as many as 1 million in the UK alone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.52,0:18:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ PERCUSSION MUSIC ♪ ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.60,0:19:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[ ♪ PERCUSSION MUSIC FADES ♪ ]
